Who needs surveillance of the contralateral carotid artery?

Iafrati MD(1), Salamipour H, Young C, Mackey WC, O'Donnell TF Jr.

Author information:
(1)Department of Surgery, New England Medical Center, Boston, Massachusetts 
02111, USA.

BACKGROUND: Although the value of carotid endarterectomy has been proven, 
postoperative surveillance remains controversial. The purpose of this study was 
to determine the natural history of disease progression in the contralateral 
carotid artery by duplex surveillance, and to assess the cost of stroke 
prevention on this contralateral side.
METHODS: Vascular laboratory records were reviewed to identify carotid 
